# Tests that cannot run in the browser test-runner. Format:
#   <path>[|<reason>]
# Skipped tests are still compiled, fetched, and displayed — but the runner
# marks them SKIP and they don't count toward fail in CI.

# Platform string asserts GLNXA64 — specific to a real Node/Linux host.
builtins/test_computer.m|asserts Node/Linux computer() string

# Assertions probe the real process cwd (package.json, numbl_test_scripts, …).
builtins/test_isfile.m|asserts against real Node cwd contents
builtins/test_isfolder.m|asserts against real Node cwd contents

# Synchronous XHR in a document context can't set timeout/responseType.
# Would need an async HTTP path through the interpreter to run here.
builtins/test_weboptions.m|synchronous XHR restrictions in browser main thread
builtins/test_websave.m|synchronous XHR restrictions in browser main thread
